Because sometimes quotes are a pain Certain tiling window status bars&hellip;
\x27
Equivalent to &rsquo; (HEX or hexidecimal is 27)
\x22
Equivalent to &quot; (HEX or hexidecimal is 22)
Example
echo -en &quot;This is nearly a sure way to print quotes: \x22Blah\x22&quot;
Result: This is nearly a sure way to print quotes: &ldquo;Blah&rdquo;
Resources ASCII table: hexidecimals of symbols, HTML number/name, etc.

See also Virtual Console
Editing files&hellip; sudov /etc/default/grub
++ GRUB_GFXMODE=1152x864x32 ++ GRUB_GFXPAYLOAD=1152x864x32 sudov /etc/grub.d/00_header
-- if [ &#34;x${GRUB_GFXMODE}&#34; = &#34;x&#34; ] ; then GRUB_GFXMODE=auto ; fi ++ if [ &#34;x${GRUB_GFXMODE}&#34; = &#34;x&#34; ] ; then GRUB_GFXMODE=1152x864x32 ; fi ++ if [ &#34;x${GRUB_GFXPAYLOAD}&#34; = &#34;x&#34; ] ; then GRUB_GFXPAYLOAD=1152x864x32 ; fi Look for: set gfxmode=${GRUB_GFXMODE}
/ to input a search term with Vim
Next line: set gfxpayload=${GRUB_GFXPAYLOAD}
Resources Ask Ubuntu: &ldquo;How do I increase console-mode resolution?&rdquo;

Find match or match grep 'match\|match2'
grep -E 'match|match2'
Find match and match grep 'match.*match2' Omit match grep -v 'match' Find first or last of line match grep &quot;^match&quot;
grep &quot;match$&quot;
Resources GNU Grep

Refresh desktop menu to add new programs, etc. vim ~/.config/openbox/menu.xml
&lt;?xml version=&#34;1.0&#34; encoding=&#34;utf-8&#34;?&gt;&lt;openbox_menu&gt;&lt;menu id=&#34;root-menu&#34; label=&#34;OpenBox 3&#34; execute=&#34;/usr/bin/obmenu-generator&#34;&gt;&lt;/menu&gt;&lt;/openbox_menu&gt; Center all new windows vim ~/.config/openbox/rc.xml
&lt;placement&gt;&lt;policy&gt;Smart&lt;/policy&gt;&lt;!-- &#39;Smart&#39; or &#39;UnderMouse&#39; --&gt;&lt;center&gt;yes&lt;/center&gt;&lt;!-- whether to place windows in the center of the free area found orthe top left corner --&gt;&lt;monitor&gt;Any&lt;/monitor&gt;&lt;!-- with Smart placement on a multi-monitor system, try to place new windowson: &#39;Any&#39; - any monitor, &#39;Mouse&#39; - where the mouse is, &#39;Active&#39; - wherethe active window is --&gt;&lt;/placement&gt;
